There is hardly ever a wait time at Smile Quest. Once I check in it usually take minutes for someone to tend to me. The staff has always been extremely nice and very informative. The doctors are amazing and never try and up-sale any treatments or procedures. They are the most humble group of dentist I've had the pleasure of knowing. I highly recommend Smile Quest Dental to everyone. Whether its simple work or major work needed. This office will satisfy all your dental needs.

< text>
Smile Quest is a great Dental Office.  My husband purchased a generous coupon at a fundraising auction for Invisalign (teeth straightening aligners).  My brother-in-law was our dentist and would accept our insurance as full payment.  However, Smile Quest was more conveniently located for the frequent dental appointments that would be needed for Invisalign. The service my husband received over the year was so fabulous that we transferred our care, including our 4 children, to Dr. Smurthwaite.  When my daughter's orthodontist could not be reached, he cared for her on a Sunday evening to treat her infection caused by her braces.  Smilequest has not only been wonderful for regular cleanings, but also for root canals, teeth extractions, and sedation. It is not uncommon for Dr. Smurthwaite to call after treatment "just to see how the patient is feeling" after major dental care.
I have never missed an appointment because Smile Quest accommodates our need to change appointments and my children love visiting the office.  The playroom and massage chairs add an inviting touch to the practice. The front staff is friendly and truly provides "excellent service." When errors on computer generated statement have occured or we had questions with our insurance, the office has always settled these issues promptly and professionally.  They are WONDERFUL!</text>

<rating>5< /rating>< text>
A year ago Klimisch made unbelievably perfect repairs on my Lexus which was rear ended and pushed into a truck so that the front was also badly damaged. In addition the work was done quickly and the I was kept well advised by telephone about schedule and progress. Klimisch provides the kind of professional and respectful service that has now disappeared from a lot of our society,
Today, when I went back to the parking lot after a visit to my physical therapist I found that the back bumper wrap around had been pulled away from the body of the car. I brought it to Klimisch for a quick estimate before deciding whether or not I should invoke insurance. It was immediately looked at and concluded that repair could be made on the spot. It took about 20 min which should have invoked a charge of about $30 at the going labor rate. I was surprisingly informed that the service was complimentary and to remember Klimisch the next time I need repairs.
This is the kind of "old fashioned" by today' standards that we are all missing dreadfully.
Thank you Klimisch< /text>

There are many reasons to people love the IV Food Co-op. Of the frequently mentioned are its quality goods (including local, seasonal produce and fresh, in-house Deli items), reasonable prices, knowledgeable Workers, cooperatively owned and operated history (dedicated to bettering the community for 47 years), and free reuseable masks and thermometers to help ease the burdens of the Covid Pandemic.<//Text>

<Name>Madeline Cant√∫< /Name>< review>
This is my go to grocery store. The produce is amazing fresh and lasts long. They also carry small packaged items that are great for day trips or toddlers. We also get some of their bulk fig bars and musli. It is one of the few places you can get good oat milk. The prices are extremely comparable to other grocery stores,
I have checked!

The only downside is that their meat selection is limited, pricey, and usually not worth the buy. I can get organic meat elsewhere. Also, while they have a great selection of natural bathroom products I always can't find exactly what I'm looking for at the right price.

I go there more than once a week. My child loves going there too!< /review>

< Review>
I got into a car accident last week and I was rear ended (thankfully no one was hurt.) The insurance company of the individual at fault gave me a list of auto body shops to choose from to get my car fixed. I was hesitant to take my car to any of the shops UNTIL I came across JP Auto Body Shop. Who could resist with all the amazing reviews?! I went ahead and called to schedule an appointment. Making an appointment was so easy and I was connected to Aaron who handles insurance claims and he was able to schedule me a date and time that worked with my schedule ( which is a huge plus for me.) I was scheduled to come in on Monday and when I arrived Juliano helped me right away! I didn't even wait more than two minutes, I parked my car and he quickly came. He helped me get my rental, I was suppose to travel to the other side of town to pick up my car. But he told me not to worry because someone would come to the shop to get me! I mean WOW that was truly helpful on my part.

I took my car in on Monday and picked up my car on Thursday (the same week.) Aaron called me and gave me frequent updates, which I highly appreciated because I am the type of person who needs to know. He went though everything with me and let me know that I was in good hands.

<date>1576380395072< /date>< rate>

<Text>Of each Chinese food place in town, this one is the best (Tokyo House has them beat but that's Japanese food and Benihana's combined)

If you were to put Golden Dragon in any populated city, it would not be worth the prices they charge for their food.

It is the best Chinese food in Ridgecrest. But you're definitely paying for it.

They were fast. They were also in a hurry and very abrupt (normal for decent Chinese food places) even with very few customers. I'll happily take that for the speed by which my food was prepared.

I had the orange chicken, fried rice lunch special as well as an a la carte shrimp chow mein.

All of it was flavorful and well prepared.

The fifth star being left off is simply... This same food would cost half what it does if it was located anywhere but Ridgecrest or they'd end up shutting down.</Text><pics>None</pics>< response>
None</response>

< Review>
The food was fantastic, as you can see in the pictures. We got the bun rieu (tomato crab noodle soup), banh cuon (rice paper), popcorn chicken, and corn milk. All were delicious and the biggest surprise was corn milk for me -- who knew corn in liquid dessert form tasted so good?

The decor and atmosphere of the restaurant is warm and modern. The painting in the main dining area is fantastic (you'll know it when you see it).

A great and affordable spot.</Review>

<name>Kalle Maines<//name><resp>None< /resp><time>1555560759316<//time>< Review>
This in an interesting restaurant. The smell upon entering is not something you can call pleasant.  It smelled like old fish sauce and a bit of old rag mixed with heavy fish broth. The food came out and it was pretty good, good enough to eat but not good enough to make me want to come back anytime soon. Most of the food came out within 5 minutes of ordering.  It makes you wonder how they get it ready so fast?! We ordered some escargot.  It was heavily garlic-spiced flavored.    If the garlic was cooked out a bit, it would have been better.< /Review>

< review>
Everything we got was very good, the sauces that accompanied the Spring rolls and the wrap it yourself meat platter was so good. A very nice balance of sweet and salty.

Parking is a pain, very limited. Service was almost nonexistent, but expected. We had to try so hard to flag down a person, but it's not a big deal.

Restaurant is clean and big, we got sat down pretty quick. Only thing I wasn't a huge fan of was the banh duc, a tad too soft, and salty.<//review>

105042781435068184937< /user_id>
<name>Linh Do<//name><time>1529541587430<//time><Rating>2< /Rating><Text>You know they give out free milk tea if you write a review right? That means you can't really trust the review system anymore! Well, I got fooled by all the advertisement. Advice to people who want to try good Vietnamese food: this is not the place!!!

Rear parking is limited, side parking is scary and weird.
Inside decor is nice.

Service is bad! They forgot about half of our order, then the waitress came out and ask us "oh the food is not out yet?" Uhmmm I don't work here girl, idk?!!!

Food:
Bun cha Hanoi is supposed to be the signature dish of any Hanoi restaurant here in OC, but they made it poorly: the meat cake was dry, the fish sauce was really salty... If you know Vietnamese cuisine you know that the sauce is the most important part of many many dishes. They failed with this signature one.
Bun dau mam tom was a 3.5/5, I have to give it to them on the mam tom though, they made a good job with the sauce on this dish. Just the cha com was terrible, it's like eating a very moist sticky rice cake being fried...
Bun ca was a disappointment! The soup isn't sour enough. It seems to me like they don't put in the effort of making the different broth for different noodle soup. Bun ca has its own kind of broth, pho has its own kind of broth, bun rieu has its own kind of broth....

In conclusion, I don't like it!!! You might get better dishes than we did maybe.... At your own risk you come in!<//Text>< Pics>
None<//Pics>

<user>115272165125261998433</user>< Text>
I really enjoy dining here at any time of the day.
It is absolutely delicious and the presentation of the food is well represented.

I was craving Bun Cha Ha Noi and found this restaraunt on yelp. I wanted to try a new restaraunt and drove here. The restaraunt is "not in your face" and from the direction I was heading, I had to make a U turn. I did not have trouble finding parking, but this place could get packed.

We were quicklyy seated and the staff were very nice and polite. We sat at the booth and it was spacious. They hire just the right amount of staff that you do not need to chase them down if you needed something. The menu was straightforward and there were photos to go along with the food items. I ordered Bun Cha Ha Noi and my mom ordered a variety platter. The food came out very quickly. The food presentation was adorable with the banana leaf and so. They put a whole bottle of water on your table for your and their convenience. The cups are cute and perfect size.

Bun Cha Ha Noi had the right amount of additives to it, it was very flavorful with vermicelli noodles and the meat were fantastic. They make it just right and perfected the dish that their was no pork smell to it. I really enjoyed it and so did my mom. I have not tried their desserts but can guarantee that their main dishes are worth the drive, at least for me since I am not around the area. I also signed up for their phone list to earn credits to receive freebies, it is a neat concept that I do not see most Vietnamese restaraunt does.

We had such a great meal, my mom asked me to drive her back here again the next time. And again, we had a good time, it was not packed when we arrived in the morning. The service, again, was excellent and the food was yummy. I highly reccommend this restaraunt.<//Text>
